# Approach
* if stack is empty or counter is 0 dont add to ans
* if stack is not empty and "(" then add to ans and increase counter++
* if stack is not empty and "(" then add to ans and decrease the counter--
* return the ans 
* simple!!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I0osO1BqiGw

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```cpp []
class Solution {
public:
    string removeOuterParentheses(string s) {
     int counter = 0;
     string ans = "";

     for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){
        if(s[i]==')') counter--;
        if(counter!=0) ans += s[i];
        if(s[i]=='(') counter++;
     }   
     return ans;
    }
};


